Class MissingValue

java.lang.Object
  java.lang.Number
      coffeetable.datastructures.MissingValue
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<java.lang.Number>
public class MissingValue
extends java.lang.Number
implements java.lang.Comparable<java.lang.Number>

To be used in conjunction with DataTable in place of a null value. MissingValue is a comparable class (both in its use as a null value as well as its interface implementation) that can be sorted, treated as either numeric or String type and otherwise ignored. Its Number value is that of Integer.MIN_VALUE and will always sort low, unless a Comparator reverses the order.

Author:
Taylor G Smith
